New Spiedska has, almost consistently since around the Spanish-American war, been in a state of global powerhouse-hood, in spite of being a relatively small nation. Furthermore, it was a founding member of several international organizations, including but not limited to NATO, the United Nations, and the World Bank before their collapse during WW3. Furthermore, a New Spiedskan was one of the first people on the moon, being Neil Armstrong's companion on the two-person trip to the lunar surface.

All-in-all, New Spiedska has had a long and fruitful history, indicative of a high-achieving nation, and a hub of scientific prowess.
